  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Examining barriers to accessing primary education in the sector of Ganaketi, Bandundu Province, Dem. Rep. of Congo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This research proposal will explore the reasons which prevent children from poor backgrounds starting or completing their primary and secondary education in the Ganaketi region of DRC. Recent research suggest that more than 2500 children in the target area are prevented from enrolling in primary school, or drop out before completing their primary education. The special problems facing girls will be a highlight of the study.  The research will draw on the local knowledge and contacts of the two partners. They are Entraide, a UK based Diaspora organisation, and ADEMA, a rural grass roots group in the Congo. The aim is to build up a complete picture of the problem and to seek solutions. Close links with civic leaders, teachers and parents will form the basis for a highly participatory project.  All learning will then be shared widely, and will feed into future plans to help more children into school, and then stay to complete their studies.</narrative>
  </description>
